body:
The [db.collection.createSearchIndex()](manual/reference/method/db.collection.createSearchIndex) method has
the following syntax:

```json
db.<COLLECTION-NAME>.createSearchIndex(
  "<INDEX-NAME>",
  "vectorSearch", 
  {
    "fields": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "path": "<FIELD-NAME>",
        "model": "voyage-3-large | voyage-3.5 | voyage-3.5-lite"
      },
      {
        "type": "filter",
        "path": "<FIELD-NAME>"
      },
      ...
    ]
  }
);
```

> **Example:** For example, to create an index that enables automated
> embeddings by using the `voyage-3-large` model for the
> `fullplot` field in the collection, run the following
> command in your terminal:
>
> ```json
> db.movies.createSearchIndex(
>   "movies_automated_embeddings",
>   "vectorSearch",
>   {
>     "fields": [
>       {
>         "type": "text",
>         "path": "fullplot",
>         "model": "voyage-3-large"
>       }
>     ]
>   }
> );
> ```

